      <memberdef kind="function" id="group__modem__ubx_1ga770650b055fd597f000a1d4f9daaf712" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>int</type>
        <definition>int modem_ubx_run_script</definition>
        <argsstring>(struct modem_ubx *ubx, struct modem_ubx_script *script)</argsstring>
        <name>modem_ubx_run_script</name>
        <param>
          <type>struct <ref refid="structmodem__ubx" kindref="compound">modem_ubx</ref> *</type>
          <declname>ubx</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>struct <ref refid="structmodem__ubx__script" kindref="compound">modem_ubx_script</ref> *</type>
          <declname>script</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Writes the ubx frame in script.request and reads back its response (if available) </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>For each ubx frame sent, the device responds in 0, 1 or both of the following ways:<orderedlist>
<listitem><para>The device sends back a UBX-ACK frame to denote &apos;acknowledge&apos; and &apos;not-acknowledge&apos;. Note: the message id of UBX-ACK frame determines whether the device acknowledged. Ex: when we send a UBX-CFG frame, the device responds with a UBX-ACK frame.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>The device sends back the same frame that we sent to it, with it&apos;s payload populated. It&apos;s used to get the current configuration corresponding to the frame that we sent. Ex: frame types such as &quot;get&quot; or &quot;poll&quot; ubx frames respond this way. This response (if received) is written to script.response.</para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
<para>This function writes the ubx frame in script.request then reads back it&apos;s response. If script.match is not NULL, then every ubx frame received from the device is compared with script.match to check if a match occurred. This could be used to match UBX-ACK frame sent from the device by populating script.match with UBX-ACK that the script expects to receive.</para>
<para>The script terminates when either of the following happens:<orderedlist>
<listitem><para>script.match is successfully received and matched.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>timeout (denoted by script.timeout) occurs. <parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>ubx</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Modem Ubx instance </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>script</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Script to be executed </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>The length of ubx frame in the script.request should not exceed UBX_FRAME_SZ_MAX </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>Modem Ubx instance must be attached to a pipe instance </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>0 if successful </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>negative errno code if failure </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
